much greater in winter and spring than in summer or fall. When averaged over all seasons, magnitudes over North America show similar ratios between levels to the previous calculations, but are overall 3-4 times smaller. This may be because of limitations (trajectory length and vertical resolution) to the current TOST-based calculation.},
author = {Tarasick, D.W. and Carey-Smith, T.K. and Hocking, W.K. and Moeini, O and He, H and Liu, J and Osman, M.K. and Thompson, A.M. and Johnson, B.J. and Oltmans, S.J. and Merrill, J.T.},
doi = {10.1016/j.atmosenv.2018.10.040},
file = {:home/pankaj/Documents/Mendeley/Tarasick et al. - 2019 - Quantifying stratosphere-troposphere transport of ozone using balloon-borne ozonesondes, radar windprofilers(3).pdf:pdf},
issn = {13522310},
journal = {Atmospheric Environment},
